-- U.S.-based stock funds attract $3.7 bln over week - Lipper
-- By Luciana Lopez
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 05:02PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, July 10 (Reuters) - Investors in U.S.-based funds committed $3.7 billion to stock funds in the week ended July 9 after adding $3.1 billion to the funds the prior week, data from Thomson Reuters' Lipper service showed on Thursday.

Stock mutual funds attracted $1.5 billion in new cash, while stock exchange-traded funds added $2.2 billion. Stock mutual funds are commonly purchased by retail investors, while stock ETFs are thought to represent the institutional investor.